    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="490"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/491.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to the Dominican
                            Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The press dispatches referred to in your January 23 seem to be exaggerated. The
                    Dominican Government informs me as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Two hundred men under Generals Desiderio Arias, Zenon Toribio and a
                            Haitian criminal crossed from Haiti into our territory to disturb the
                            peace; they are now in Santiago Cruz and the Dominican Government is
                            sending a strong force against them. The movement in question has no
                            importance except that it is being aided by Haiti.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>An American receivership inspector from the region in question confirms the
                    Government statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
